i love poetry here is a short one i wrote as i lay resting you tapped me upon the shoulder in that familiar way i inhaled and let you back into my soul as you walked through the colored corridors of my mind i wish you would remind me more often just what we had planned to do this time around the world with its many tricks i m satisfied to sit and watch to pretend that it s all for my pleasure to twist my self into believing this new found truth true work comes from a true soul one that has the heart to reward itself and like a swift wind you rustled my leaves and went on your way i am only a tree you see i have no choice but to stay where i am next time stay a little longer dear friend together we can fly perhaps someday i too shall be like the wind free to play upon your curls and sing my song the tree in me knows from record the folly in such excitement it must be a sin why you come around to ask well i am a tree and i should love to be a tree the simplicity of the wind it cannot be explained some of us have the simplicity of the wind i wish i knew my true sin i would live to be a windy tree i love poetry also i really love the first half best up to the line you rustled my leaves and went on your way just me though it is good The Amber Spyglass Phaedo Time Out of Mind Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Duties of the Heart Simone Weil Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Damn Yankees Wolfrider Summa Theologiae Incarnations of Immortality One Tree Hill (TV series) Merit Bhagavad Gita We Belong Together Immortality Sin Religion Original sin Frankie Laine Aerial (dance move) Theodicy The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan Philo She Loves You Charles Grandison Finney Aladdin (1992 film) Mojave people Meat Loaf Hymn Sant Mat Virtual Realm John Wesley Datalore (TNG episode) Prince Edmund (Blackadder) EastEnders Zohar The Invisibles The Dunciad Love Socrates Shaggy dog story Another Side of Bob Dylan Carrie Jacobs-Bond Theory of conduct Alfred Edward Housman Cardcaptor Sakura Nashv